   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Once Adobe Sign and the Power eSignature service are integrated, you can create a
         transaction. To create a transaction, you must prepare a transaction payload. Call the
         following API to get the exact transaction payload field data:</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Method</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">GET</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Endpoint</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">/settings</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Request Parameter</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">signProvider: Select Adobe Sign from the drop-down list.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Response</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">This API returns a transaction object with each field's settings, such as
                           which fields are required, optional, or not supported, the data type, and
                           the name and description of the fields.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">After preparing a transaction payload, call the following API to create a transaction:</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Method</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">POST</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Endpoint</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">/transactions</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Request Body</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <ul id="ul_ikx_qzf_vcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">signProvider: Select Adobe Sign from the drop-down list.</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Payload: Enter payload.<p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Sample
                              Payload</b>
                              </p>
                              <pre xml:space="preserve" id="pre_jkx_qzf_vcc" class="- topic/pre ">{
    "name": "Agreement Document",
    "recipients": [
        {
            "firstName": "First",
            "lastName": "Last",
            "email": "flast@Power.com",
            "signerType": "SIGNER",
            "index": "0"
        }
    ]
}</pre>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">File: Select the document.</li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Response</uicontrol>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">This API returns a transaction ID, which you can use to send the
                           transaction to the recipients.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
